\b \cf0 Steps button
\b0 \
Here, you can edit the notes and other parameter of each step. \
A piano keyboard shows all the possible notes. \
The grid next to the keyboard can be clicked with a mouse to input notes and has scroll bars to move around it.\
The green buttons allow you to edit various parameters for each step:\
The 
\b notes
\b0  button displays a 3 octave keyboard (it is only 2 octaves on the other buttons). \
It also displays a checkbox: 
\b MIDI learn notes/veloicities - starting at step 1
\b0 . When this is switched on, any MIDI notes and velocities received on any MIDI channels will be recorded into the steps of the sequencer.  The new notes will be displayed on the screen.  \
This is useful adding a pattern played on a MIDI keyboard.\
The 
\b velocity
\b0  button displays the velocity values for each step, and the 
\b Velocity o/p range
\b0 , which rescales the velocity to within a certain output range.\
